main event: On 10th February 1953, unidentified radar targets were sighted in the vicinity of Misawa AFB, Japan. Despite visual confirmation attempts, the objects were not seen by aircraft, but were seen and plotted on ground radar.
interesting points: The radar targets were sighted at 1629Z on 9CA search scope.
Aircraft scrambled to intercept the targets at 1610Z, but the objects were not visually confirmed.
Unidentified interference was noted by CPS scope and ground operators, suggesting a technologically unexplained phenomenon.
The objects were reported to be moving at approximately 50 knots, with definite radar returns lasting 1 minute.
The evaluating officers refrained from attempting an evaluation until a written report confirming and elaborating on the incident was received.
